author: COMSOL
description: This tutorial illustrates how to model electrothermal actuation of a microdevice. It uses the Joule Heating interface to simulate the heating of an actuator caused by an electric voltage applied to the device. Thermal expansion is manually added using the equation view. This example uses the programming operation in the geometry sequence to consider different geometry cases.
